9
00:00:26,193 --> 00:00:30,060
唐顿庄园
第四季  第八集

10
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:37,160
我想Drewe知道我们来了
I assume Drewe knows we're coming.

11
00:00:37,180 --> 00:00:39,100
是的 我昨天送了便条
Yes. I sent a note yesterday.

12
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:41,160
那些猪好些了吗
So have the pigs recovered, do you think?

13
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:46,487
刚开始它们有点吓到我
They look in good shape to me,

14
00:00:46,488 --> 00:00:48,020
不过现在好多了
after the shock of their arrival.

15
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:50,140
可是他怎么不来检查下
But why didn't he check to see

16
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,180
猪夜里饮用的水够不够
... they all had water before he left for the night?

17
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,020
他可能以为把水槽里装满了就行了
Maybe he thought a full trough was enough.

18
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:55,980
他也没想到这些猪把水槽踢翻了
He wasn't to know they'd kick it over.

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,229
Branson先生说的对
Mr Branson is right.

20
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:58,080
他应该再检查一遍的
He should have made sure.

21
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,220
你也该如此
You would have done.

22
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,120
你知道怎么养猪吗
Where did you learn about pigs?

23
00:01:01,140 --> 00:01:03,180
我们在紫衫农场一直都有养猪 夫人
We've always had pigs at Yew Tree, m'lady.

24
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,220
不是很多 但也足够摸清它们的秉性了
Not many, but enough to learn their ways.

25
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:07,160
还好你养过
Thank heavens you did.

26
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:12,020
你找到接管这事的人了吗
So, have you found a man to take over?

27
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,200
还没
Not yet.

28
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:18,220
不过我想知道 你对这工作感兴趣吗
First, we'd like to know if you'd want the job.

29
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:20,030
我吗 你指的是我去喂养
Me? You mean I'm to manage

30
00:01:20,031 --> 00:01:23,060
庄园地产上的和我们自己农场的猪吗
the pigs for the estate, as well as my farm?

31
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,140
这要求是多了点
It's asking a lot.

32
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,140
我可以的 如果你们确定的话
I can do it. If you're sure.

33
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:31,080
我们可以试试 再看怎么继续干下去
Let's give it a try, see how we get on.

34
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:33,100
我很感激 夫人
I'm very grateful, m'lady.

35
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:37,060
这是你们家族给我的第二次恩惠了
This is the second good turn I've received from your family,

36
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:40,040
我只希望有一天可以回报
and I just hope I can pay back a favour one day.

37
00:01:40,060 --> 00:01:41,140
你真的太善良了
How nice of you.

38
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,140
我不知道这算不算恩惠
I don't know if it's much of a favour.

39
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,692
我们给你的活太多了
We're giving you a lot of work.

40
00:01:45,693 --> 00:01:47,140
工作就像老龄
Work's like old age, m'lady.

41
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:50,240
虽然让人厌恶 但也不可或缺
The worst thing in the world except for the alternative.

42
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,200
是我罢了
It's only me.

43
00:01:58,220 --> 00:02:00,650
我总认为这个问候语
I always feel that greeting betrays

44
00:02:00,651 --> 00:02:03,080
有点自轻自贱的意味
such a lack of self worth.

45
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:07,140
你今天怎么样
How are we today?

46
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,384
亲爱的 别这样对我说话
My dear, please stop

47
00:02:08,385 --> 00:02:11,140
显着我像个无药可救的孩子
talking to me as if I were a child past hope.

48
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:13,140
好吧 你现在感觉如何
Very well. How are you feeling?

49
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,180
像Manette医生似得
Like Doctor Manette.

50
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:16,180
{\a6}Manette医生-双城记里的人物 在长期囚禁下未老先衰

51
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:18,120
我要是再不出门
If I don't get out of this house soon,

52
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:20,140
恐怕我就只记得自己的岁数了
I shall remember nothing but my number.

53
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,592
要不我们下午走去庄园吧
Then why don't we walk to the Abbey this afternoon,

54
00:02:22,593 --> 00:02:23,200
可以吗
if it's fine?

55
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:25,220
听听Robert的美国之行
Hear how Robert's getting on in America.

56
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:28,180
那真的是唤作茶壶圆顶绯闻吗
Is it really called the Tea Pot Dome scandal?

57
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:29,180
{\a6}1920-1923年在美国发生的著名受贿丑闻

58
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:31,100
- 听起来不可思议   - 关于什么的
- It seems so unlikely.  - What's it about?

59
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:34,240
- 还不是老一套 无非是贿赂跟腐败呗
- What is it always about? Bribery and corruption.

60
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,060
拿了好处 允许私企
Taking money to allow private companies

61
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:42,160
在政府的土地开采石油
to drill for oil on Government land.

62
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:44,180
Levinson先生的公司是其一吗
Mr Levinson has one of these companies?

63
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,060
我想是如此
I assume so.

64
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,410
你见过他吗
Have you ever met him?

65
00:02:47,411 --> 00:02:49,140
就一次 在当年的婚礼上
Once. At the wedding.

66
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,080
但那一次就足够了
And once was quite enough.

67
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:55,055
我没法告诉你那有多令人兴奋呢
I can't tell you how thrilling that sounds.

68
00:02:55,056 --> 00:02:56,180
我会等你
I'll be waiting for you.

69
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,040
我们会度过美好的一天
We'll have such a lovely day.

70
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,060
- 那是谁   - 一个朋友而已
- Who was that? - No-one. Just a friend.

71
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,100
你得为义卖多出点力了
You have to pull your weight with the bazaar.

72
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,060
感觉这都成我一人的事了
It seems to have crept up on me.

73
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:09,020
Robert表哥经常组织这些事吗
Does Cousin Robert usually do it?

74
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,100
是的 村子里的人互相看不顺眼
He does. Half the village hates the other half

75
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,920
只有他能阻止
and he's the only one who can stop them

76
00:03:12,921 --> 00:03:15,020
他们互相斗嘴了
tearing each other's throats out.

77
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:31,140
真羡慕 这是真手艺啊
I admire that. It's a real skill.

78
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:35,160
Molesley先生
Mr Molesley, erm,

79
00:03:35,161 --> 00:03:37,240
你曾经做过贴身男仆是吗
is it true that you were a valet?

80
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,120
还是服伺已故的Crawley先生是吗
For the late Mr Crawley?

81
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:42,020
是的 在此之前是Crawley先生母亲的管家
And butler to his mother before that.

82
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,511
最近我的生活很不顺
I've come down in the world.

83
00:03:44,512 --> 00:03:46,100
你会再爬起来的
You can climb up again.

84
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,000
也许吧 但生活有时会
Maybe. But life kicks the

85
00:03:48,001 --> 00:03:51,160
踢你一脚呢 对吧
stuffing out of you sometimes, doesn't it?

86
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:55,220
噢 那我可跌下不止一次了
Oh, I've had my stuffing kicked out more than once.

87
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:58,100
我曾醒来想着这到底有没有意义呢
I've woken and wondered if there was any point to it.

88
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:02,080
现在呢 我是伯爵夫人的贴身女仆
Yet here I am, lady's maid to a countess.

89
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:05,080
所以 一切都会好的
So, it can happen.

90
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,040
你现在让我很好奇了
Now you've made me curious.

91
00:04:08,060 --> 00:04:11,200
我也在好奇一些事 你也许能给我答案
I'm curious about something and you could help me.

92
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:17,100
你知道Bates夫妇吵架了吗
Do you know if Mr and Mrs Bates have had a falling out?

93
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:20,980
Bates夫妻吗 不大可能吧
Mr and Mrs Bates? That doesn't sound very likely.

94
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,020
你可以把那个机器挪开吗
Can I ask you to put that machine away?

95
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:26,040
- 我们马上要准备茶了   - 好的
- We'll be laying for tea in a minute. - Of course.

96
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,200
大家都准备好仆人的茶了吗
Is everything ready for the servants' tea?

97
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,210
到底是我一人 还是大家的
Oh, is it just me or do we

98
00:04:33,211 --> 00:04:35,020
花销都比过去多了一倍
have twice the bills we used to?

99
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,040
Ivy 这是你的
Ivy, this is for you.

100
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:41,100
你找到去除水壶污垢的蛎壳粉了吗
Did you find those oyster shells for the kettle?

101
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,000
我已经放进去了 得等一会 里面都是生水垢
I've put them in. About time. It were full of scale.

102
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:51,020
那信里到底写的什么啊
What in God's name was that about?

103
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,258
别小题大做 她只是
Don't rise to it. She just

104
00:04:52,259 --> 00:04:54,180
故意想让我们觉得她日子很有趣呢
wants us to think her life's interesting.

105
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,618
有啥趣事吗
Anything interesting?

106
00:05:00,619 --> 00:05:02,040
我在读郡的政报
I'm reading about County Politics.

107
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:04,240
他们正在招募地方议会的候选人
They're looking for candidates for the local Council.

108
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,060
你怎么不自荐呢
Why don't you put yourself forward?

109
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:10,120
但我最近没去了解时政 没有把握
But what are my politics these days? I'm not sure.

110
00:05:10,140 --> 00:05:12,120
你总可以了解些的
You could always read a bit about it.

111
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,879
这个房间里你找不到几本
You won't find many books

112
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,220
自由主义思想的书籍
on the Liberal ideals in this room.

113
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:19,120
更别提关于社会主义的了
And nothing at all about Socialism.

114
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:22,160
要是你真想明天把我载到瑟斯克
If you're serious about driving me to Thirsk tomorrow,

115
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:25,040
也许我们可以找到一些那方面的书
perhaps we might find some then.

116
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,020
你现在好多了吗 奶奶
Are you better now, Granny?

117
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,980
你要是来看望过我 你就知道了
If you'd been to see me, you'd know.

118
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,980
别取笑我了 我又不是那照顾人的料
Don't bully me. I'm not up to it.

119
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,100
是啊 Rosamund都告诉我了
No. Rosamund told me.

120
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:42,100
什么时候 她说什么了
When? What did she say?

121
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:45,240
你只是需要点关爱罢了
Only that you needed a little cherishing, that's all.

122
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,020
这么说Drewe接受了你提议的工作
So Mr Drewe's accepted your officer.

123
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,140
我很高兴
I'm so pleased.

124
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:53,040
Drewe一家在紫衫农场做了很多年
The Drewes have been at Yew Tree Farm for many years.

125
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:53,960
我以为你要说他
I suppose you think

126
00:05:53,961 --> 00:05:56,020
是感情用事的人呢 Blake先生
that's sentimental bosh, Mr Blake.

127
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,140
别为难他 奶奶
Don't be too hard on him, Granny.

128
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,920
Blake先生比他给我们的
Mr Blake has a softer side

129
00:05:59,921 --> 00:06:01,140
第一映象要友善多了
than we first gave him credit for.

130
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,471
在我们启程去伦敦前
I'm relieved to hear I am redeemed

131
00:06:02,472 --> 00:06:04,220
知道你原谅了我真是个宽慰
before we leave for London.

132
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:07,060
希望你也原谅我
I hope I'm forgiven, too.

133
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,992
我知道你第一次见我时
I know you thought me very snobbish

134
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:10,140
觉得我很势利
when you first arrived.

135
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,688
我没怪你 我来时
I don't blame you. Given my work,

136
00:06:12,689 --> 00:06:15,140
可是作为国家敌人的特使
I came as an envoy of the enemy.

137
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,700
是我们来早了吗
Are we too early?

138
00:06:16,701 --> 00:06:18,240
保姆 把他们抱进来吧
Bring them in, Nanny.

139
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,100
我想没人介意吧
I don't think anyone will mind.

140
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:24,060
你爸爸可能会 不过他不在这里 哪来抱怨
Your Papa might, but he isn't here to complain.

141
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:27,020
等一会 宝贝 妈妈放下杯子
One moment, darling, while Mummy puts away her cup.

142
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:30,160
来 过来这里 我宝宝 你好啊 小子
Oh, here, let me. Hello there.

143
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:32,100
对 真乖
Oh, it's all right.

144
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:35,180
小家伙长得真壮实
He's turning into quite a bruiser.

145
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,514
我得走了
Yes, and I must go.

146
00:06:36,515 --> 00:06:38,120
留下来吃晚餐 妈妈
Stay and have some dinner, Mama.

147
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:39,382
你不必换晚装
You needn't change.

148
00:06:39,383 --> 00:06:41,040
不了 谢谢 亲爱的 真的不用
No. Thank you, my dear, but no.

149
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:44,220
你应该要更衣了 我则该走了
You should change and I should go.

150
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,302
你下楼时能不能帮我
When you go down,

151
00:06:51,303 --> 00:06:53,040
带个话给Hughes夫人
can you give a message to Mrs Hughes?

152
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:54,080
当然好
Of course.

153
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:56,180
Gillingham昨天打电话过来
Lord Gillingham telephoned today.

154
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,140
明天晚上他想回家之前
He wants to break his journey home.

155
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,000
顺便过来这里
Tomorrow night.

156
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:02,220
他又来了吗
He'll be here again?

157
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:07,020
是的 我真不该鼓励他
You're right. I shouldn't encourage him,

158
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:11,160
可是我想不到别的话叫他不要来
but I couldn't think what to say to persuade him not to.

159
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:14,240
你会觉得我很懦弱吗
Do you think me very feeble?

160
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,140
不是的 夫人
It's not that, m'lady.

161
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:21,120
那怎么了
Then what is it?

162
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,040
Anna
Anna?

163
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,003
这不是你该烦恼的事
It's nothing to bother you with.

164
00:07:30,004 --> 00:07:31,080
拜托麻烦我吧
Please bother me.

165
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:38,160
要是我告诉你 你得保证你听过就罢
If I did, you'd have to promise to do nothing about it.

166
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:41,140
可这关Gillingham伯爵什么事呢
But how does this concern Lord Gillingham?

167
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,345
不是的 夫人
It doesn't, m'lady.

168
00:07:43,346 --> 00:07:46,240
这跟Gillingham伯爵无关
It's nothing to do with Lord Gillingham himself.

169
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,180
- 那   - 是他的男仆 夫人
- But then...  - It's his man, m'lady.

170
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:53,160
他的仆人 跟他一起旅行的Green先生
His servant, Mr Green, who travels with him.

171
00:07:58,160 --> 00:08:00,120
噢 天哪
Oh, my God.

172
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,020
- 可是警察应该   - 不可以
- But the police ought to...  - No!

173
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,485
我必须要告诉Gillingham伯爵
I must tell Lord Gillingham.

174
00:08:05,486 --> 00:08:06,240
不 夫人 你答应过的
No, m'lady, you promised.

175
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,000
Bates先生还不知道是他
Mr Bates doesn't know it was him.

176
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,080
但他来的次数越多
But the more he comes here,

177
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:13,000
Bates先生越有可能发现他是犯人
the more likely it is that Mr Bates will find out.

178
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,548
那我就电话告诉他
Then I'll telephone him and

179
00:08:14,549 --> 00:08:17,040
不要过来了 或者别带Green先生来
