可以去约克  我希望你不介意
into York tomorrow. I hope you don't mind.

719
00:32:08,460 --> 00:32:11,420
你在这又没事可做  我为什么会介意
You've got no duties here. Why should I mind?

720
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:14,380
如果你不反对 我一大早就出发
I'll set off first thing, if you've no objection.

721
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,600
请自便 Bates先生
Be my guest, Mr Bates.

722
00:32:15,620 --> 00:32:18,620
我还是不知道你为什么不去纽约
I still don't understand why you're not in New York,

723
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:21,420
所以我又能对约克说什么呢
so I can hardly object to York.

724
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,520
玩的开心
Enjoy yourself.

725
00:32:35,580 --> 00:32:37,480
很好 做的好 女士们
Very good. Well done, ladies.

726
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:46,440
- 我能试试吗   - 现在还不行
- Can I have a go? - It's not ready yet.

727
00:32:46,460 --> 00:32:48,480
至少 你有点矮 不是吗
Anyway, you're a bit of a shrimp, aren't you?

728
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:49,640
我是矮 但我有肌肉
I'm a shrimp with muscles, me.

729
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:52,440
我们周六见分晓吧
We'll find that out on Saturday.

730
00:32:52,460 --> 00:32:54,534
我一直不喜欢这些
I've never had a go on one of those.

731
00:32:54,535 --> 00:32:56,420
你不适合玩这些
It's not your sort of thing.

732
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:58,130
再来些三明治和啤酒
More sandwiches and more beer.

733
00:32:58,131 --> 00:32:59,580
就像是受蝗虫灾了似的
It's like a plague of locusts.

734
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:01,025
忙吗 Molesley先生
Busy, Mr Molesley?

735
00:33:01,026 --> 00:33:01,580
我喜欢集市
I like the bazaar.

736
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:03,580
我很享受这个  我希望你也能喜欢
I always enjoy it. I hope you will.

737
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:05,580
你能帮帮她吗 Molesley先生
Can't you help her too, Mr Molesley?

738
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:08,400
噢 离远点 你这厚脸皮的家伙
Oh, get off with you, you cheeky devil.

739
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:14,303
Alfred周六要来 是吗
Alfred's coming Saturday, in't he?

740
00:33:14,304 --> 00:33:15,540
你怎么知道的
How do you know that?

741
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,570
我听到你和Hughes女士的谈话了
I heard you and Mrs Hughes talking.

742
00:33:17,571 --> 00:33:19,580
噢 我 我正想 跟你说呢
Well I, I were going to mention it,

743
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:22,560
因为我觉得你最好避开他
because I wondered if you'd rather be away.

744
00:33:22,580 --> 00:33:23,900
那工作怎么办
What about all the work?

745
00:33:23,901 --> 00:33:25,580
噢 到时候也干的差不多了
Oh, it's mostly done by then.

746
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:29,580
如果你想避开他 我不介意的
If you'd rather avoid him, I won't mind.

747
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:31,540
我能去看看Mason先生吗
Could I go and see Mr Mason?

748
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:33,420
可以啊 这是个好主意
That's a good idea.

749
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:36,520
去多久都行  注意安全就好
Stay away as late as you like. Just to be safe.

750
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:40,480
为什么这么着急
But why the urgency?

751
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:41,424
我说不清楚
I can't explain,

752
00:33:41,425 --> 00:33:43,580
但如果你知道的话 你会明白的
but I swear if you knew, you'd approve.

753
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:45,805
怎么了 发生了什么
What this? What's happened?

754
00:33:45,806 --> 00:33:47,380
Mary要去伦敦
Mary has to go to London.

755
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,460
没什么事  我明晚就回来
It's no big thing. I'll be back tomorrow night.

756
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:50,580
- 我能一起去吗   - 不行
- Can I come? - No.

757
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:51,750
为什么
Well, why not?

758
00:33:51,751 --> 00:33:53,620
因为妈妈需要你在这帮她
Because Mama needs you here.

759
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:55,640
再见  再见 Rose
Goodbye, then. Bye, Rose.

760
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:57,490
你想在我那住一宿吗
Do you want to stay at the house?

761
00:33:57,491 --> 00:33:58,580
我可以打电话安排一下
I'll telephone if you do.

762
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,420
行吗  谢谢你
Could you? You're an angel.

763
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:02,620
我让Mead去他斯温登的姐姐那
I told Mead he could visit his sister in Swindon,

764
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:04,754
他们尽可能的安排好的
but they'll do the best they can.

765
00:34:04,755 --> 00:34:05,600
谢谢你了
Thank you.

766
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:09,400
真神秘
How mysterious.

767
00:34:27,460 --> 00:34:28,580
出什么问题了吗
Is anything wrong?

768
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:31,480
车子不转了 我朋友去找人求救了
The car's packed in, my friend's gone for help.

769
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:32,970
我帮你看看吧
Would you like me to have a look?

770
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:34,440
我不想耽误你的时间
I don't want to hold you up.

771
00:34:34,460 --> 00:34:36,560
我也没事  我是去斯基普顿见
I've no appointment. I was on my way to Skipton

772
00:34:36,580 --> 00:34:39,560
供应商比较价格的
to see some suppliers and compare prices.

773
00:34:39,580 --> 00:34:41,460
挺不错的
How impressive.

774
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:42,042
我以为
I thought that

775
00:34:42,043 --> 00:34:45,420
当代理人成为有钱人的表亲或是女婿的话
when the agent was a cousin or son-in-law,

776
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:47,640
他就不用再为生活奔波了 反正有别人干
he had free shooting for life, but others did the work.

777
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:50,520
引用我老婆的奶奶的话
To quote my wife's grandmother,

778
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:53,380
你一定是读过有关社会主义的报纸的
you've been reading Socialist newspapers again.

779
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,560
你说对了
You should know.

780
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,440
这样好吗
Is this wise?

781
00:35:00,460 --> 00:35:02,560
你可能听过有关于我的故事 但只是一部分
You've heard some of my story, but not all of it.

782
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:05,620
我以前是在唐顿做司机的
I came to Downton to be the chauffeur.

783
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:07,640
现在
Now...

784
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,620
可口的午饭
That was a splendid luncheon.

785
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:16,295
这让我大开眼界了
Quite a change for me.

786
00:35:16,296 --> 00:35:17,600
噢 我才不相信呢
Oh, I can't believe that.

787
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:20,480
是真的  我吃的简直是病号饭
It's true. I eat nothing but nursery food.

788
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:22,878
也许你需要一个新的厨师
Perhaps you need a new cook.

789
00:35:22,879 --> 00:35:23,620
这不是厨师的错
It's not her fault.

790
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:25,500
是我不知道该点些什么
I never know what to order.

791
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:28,460
人们经常对男人说 你要比老婆先死
A husband is told so often he's going to die first,

792
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:31,460
否则你是不知道要怎么独自一人生活下去的
you never think you're going to have to manage on your own.

793
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,690
我想Crawley医生还在的话
I doubt Doctor Crawley

794
00:35:33,691 --> 00:35:34,520
他会做的很好
would have managed any better.

795
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:36,460
我真惊讶他是个医生
I'm so interested he was a doctor.

796
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:37,840
我曾想自学医术
I wanted to study medicine myself,

797
00:35:37,841 --> 00:35:39,540
但是我父亲真的不认为
but my father didn't really...

798
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:43,420
不认为这是个绅士的职位
Didn't see it as a profession for a gentleman.

799
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,540
我想他也不至于这么说
I don't believe he'd have gone that far.

800
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:48,640
但他是确实不认为这是个适合贵族的职位
But he didn't think it quite suitable for a peer, no.

801
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:52,520
我应该试着举个例子反驳他
I must try and find an example to rebut that.

802
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:56,520
我该走了
Well, I must be going.

803
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:59,580
我送你吧 我的车子就停在外面
Let me take you. My car's outside.

804
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:01,440
我走回去就行
I can easily walk.

805
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:03,480
请让我载您一程
I'd like to. Please.

806
00:36:03,500 --> 00:36:05,540
那么谢谢了
Then...thank you.

807
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,460
我也得走了
I should go too, Granny.

808
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:11,460
别走
No. Stay.

809
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:13,440
我有话想对你说
I want to speak to you.

810
00:36:16,580 --> 00:36:19,440
你结婚的时候还是个司机吗
So were you still the chauffeur when you married?

811
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,580
说来话长
That's a long story.

812
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:25,540
你的事都是说来话长
Everything with you's a long story.

813
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:27,560
这个故事有个美好的结局
That one had a happy ending.

814
00:36:28,580 --> 00:36:30,640
至少有段时间是
For a time, anyway.

815
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:35,440
我知道她死了
I know she died.

816
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:39,420
很抱歉
I'm so sorry.

817
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:42,520
她一定是一个不平常而又独立的人
She must have been a very unusual and independent person.

818
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:44,620
你说得对
You could say that again.

819
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:48,887
他们让你留下来
It's nice that they asked you to stay,

820
00:36:48,888 --> 00:36:50,560
在这里谋生是件好事
to make your life here.

821
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:55,440
我有一个小女儿 这看上去是件正确的事
I have a little daughter, and it seemed the right thing.

822
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,460
这让我对这家人的看法更温和了
Still, it makes me take a kinder view of the family.

823
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:02,420
你以前对这家人有什么不满意吗
Oh? What do you have against them?

824
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,540
什么都没有
Nothing.

825
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:07,540
但是 照例 我对他们这类人没什么好感
But, as a rule, I don't really warm to their type.

826
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:09,580
我不相信人的阶级
I don't believe in types.

827
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,640
我相信人本身
I believe in people.

828
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:14,400
现在来试试
Now give it a try.

829
00:37:24,420 --> 00:37:28,400
真的很谢谢你  谢谢
I really am very grateful. Thank you.

830
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:46,540
我不怎么说这个
I don't often say it,

831
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:48,620
但是Rosamund是对的
but Rosamund is right.

832
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:52,640
我不知道Drewe先生
I do not know this Mr...Mr Drewe,...

833
00:37:54,560 --> 00:37:57,440
即使他是你说的那样
..But even if he is everything you say,

834
00:37:57,460 --> 00:37:59,540
让孩子留在这
to keep the child here

835
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:01,446
会像离你脑袋很近的
would be like a permanent

836
00:38:01,447 --> 00:38:04,540
达摩克利斯之剑一样
sword of Damocles, inches from your head.

837
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:08,400
我无法忍受把他送走的想法
But I can't bear the thought of giving it away.

838
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:11,600
让他在瑞士长大对不对
And is it right that it should grow up Swiss?

839
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:15,440
瑞士可以提供一切
Well, Switzerland has everything to offer,...

840
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:18,500
除了日常对话少了点
..Except perhaps conversation.

841
00:38:18,520 --> 00:38:21,440
但至少缺了也不影响
And one can learn to live without that.

842
00:38:21,460 --> 00:38:23,580
如果Michael出现了呢
And if Michael turns up?

843
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:27,460
我的建议就是 和他重新开始
Well, if you want my advice, start again.

844
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:29,580
我会负担一切
Now, I will pay for everything.

845
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,440
Rosamund姨母说她会负担一切
Aunt Rosamund said she would.

846
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:35,460
事实上你会无法忍受
You'll be quite enough in her debt as it is.

847
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,460
欠她哪怕一分钱
Take any more,

848
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:41,420
她会开始收严苛的年贡
and she'll start exacting annual tribute.

849
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:45,460
你的儿子们做什么  我认为他们是有工作的
What do your sons do? I assume they do something.

850
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:48,420
记得我在晚宴时遇到Larry吗
Remember I met Larry at that dinner?

851
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:50,400
别提醒我了
Ah, don't remind me.

852
00:38:50,420 --> 00:38:52,460
他们是有工作
They do work.

853
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,540
Larry是银行职员Tim是外交官
Larry's in banking and Tim's in the diplomatic,

854
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:58,520
没什么令人吃惊的  那你的儿子呢
so nothing very startling there. What about yours?

855
00:38:58,540 --> 00:39:01,420
Matthew是个律师
Matthew was a lawyer.

856
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:02,600
他辞职了吗
Oh, has he given it up?

857
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,520
他
He's...

858
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:08,460
他死了
He's dead.

859
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:10,540
我以为你知道
I thought you would know that.

860
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:12,560
天呐
Oh, good God.

861
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,470
真的非常抱歉
I'm terribly sorry.

862
00:39:15,471 --> 00:39:17,380
我刚才忘了你是谁
I... I'd forgotten for a moment who you were.

863
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,520
请不要担心
Don't worry. Please.

864
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:24,460
Mary呢  我以为我今天可以见到她
How is Mary? I do wish I could have seen her today.

865
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:25,929
虽然慢了些
Well, slow to start with,

866
00:39:25,930 --> 00:39:28,480
但是我很高兴 她走上了正轨
but now she's on her way, which I'm glad of.

867
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:30,580
- 我听说他们很合适   - 是的
- I heard they were well suited.   - Yes.

868
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:34,420
他们曾经很幸福 这让分离变得更糟糕
They were happy, which makes the parting worse,

869
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:37,600
但这样的爱情 最终都会带给人力量
but gives you strength in the end, as we know.

870
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,560
那是你  但不是我
You maybe. Not me.

871
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:48,500
Mearton女士和我不是刻意要在一起
Lady Merton and I were not exactly meant to be together.

872
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:52,420
那时候 我们像其他人那样挣扎着活着
We struggled on, of course, as everyone did in those days,

873
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:55,480
但是我现在不确定它是否明智
but I'm not sure now how sensible it was.

874
00:39:56,540 --> 00:39:59,101
我嫉妒你 你美好的记忆
I envy you, your wonderful memories,

875
00:39:59,102 --> 00:40:01,520
但是我不能觊觎它们
but I can't pretend to match them.

876
00:40:19,420 --> 00:40:20,600
Ross先生还在这么
Is Mr Ross here yet?

877
00:40:20,620 --> 00:40:24,460
- 请问您是谁   - Rose的表姐
- Who shall I say is calling?    - Rose's cousin.

878
00:40:42,525 --> 00:40:46,460
Mary女士
Lady Mary.Huh.

879
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,580
我还在想是不是你
I was wondering if it would be you.

880
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:50,540
你怎么知道会有人来找你
How did you know someone was coming?

881
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:52,540
Rose打过电话
Rose telephoned.

882
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:55,560
她说她告诉了你我们准备确定日期
She said she'd told you we were about to set the date.

883
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:58,620
我煮了茶  你要来一杯么
I just made some tea. Would you like a cup?

884
00:40:58,640 --> 00:41:00,400
谢谢
Thank you.

885
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:06,420
我猜你来是想说弗林特郡的老爷
I suppose you're here to say that Lord Flintshire

886
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:09,540
发现他有个黑人女婿很荒谬
would find the prospect of a black son-in-law preposterous.

887
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:11,520
您父亲会很赞同
And your father would agree.

888
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:14,600
说句实在话 比起忍受你的肤色
To be fair to Papa, he'd find your being a band singer

889
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:17,460
他更难接受你是一个乐队歌手的事实
even harder to swallow than your colour.

890
00:41:21,560 --> 00:41:24,560
Ross先生 你确定吗
Mr Ross, are you sure about this?

891
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:29,460
婚姻是一项挑战 即使每个人都想要它
Marriage is a challenge, even when everyone wants it.

892
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:32,580
即使每个人都祈祷你能幸福
Even if everyone prays you'll be happy.

893
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,648
你的意思是在我们这件事上
You mean in our case,

894
00:41:34,649 --> 00:41:36,540
他们一直在努力地拆散我们
they'll all be trying to pull us apart.

895
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:39,400
每时每刻
Every hour of every day.

896
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:52,440
告诉我 你觉得她爱你吗
Tell me, do you think she loves you?

897
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:55,420
你不相信我们吗
Don't you believe in us?

898
