1086
00:52:33,700 --> 00:52:36,920
很现代 很有趣
Very modern...and very interesting.

1087
00:52:37,880 --> 00:52:39,760
家里怎么样
How's it been here?

1088
00:52:39,780 --> 00:52:41,820
不大有趣也不大现代
Not very interesting and not very modern.

1089
00:52:42,820 --> 00:52:44,865
Carson 你好 Bates
Carson. Hello, Bates.

1090
00:52:44,866 --> 00:52:45,760
有没有挂念我啊
Have you missed me?

1091
00:52:46,780 --> 00:52:48,760
我倒是蛮挂念你们
Because I've certainly missed you.

1092
00:52:48,780 --> 00:52:50,780
很高兴您回家 老爷
Good to see you back, m'lord.

1093
00:52:53,780 --> 00:52:54,900
你回来了
You're back.

1094
00:52:55,920 --> 00:52:57,900
真不敢相信
I can't believe it.

1095
00:52:57,920 --> 00:53:00,940
我梦想这一刻多时了
If you knew how many times I'd imagined this scene.

1096
00:53:08,780 --> 00:53:11,700
这是个小慰劳  咱们有段时间没见了
This is a treat. It's been a while.

1097
00:53:12,900 --> 00:53:14,800
我很抱歉一直没来看你
I'm sorry if I've stayed away.

1098
00:53:14,820 --> 00:53:17,840
别抱歉 你不该道歉 别在这里
Nay, no apologies. Not from you. Not here.

1099
00:53:17,860 --> 00:53:19,880
你是我的儿媳妇
You're my daughter-in-law,

1100
00:53:19,900 --> 00:53:22,860
是我儿子为我留下的唯一的亲人
you're all that I've got left of my son.

1101
00:53:22,880 --> 00:53:26,720
不论你回不回来 这儿都是你的家
Whether you come here or not, this is your home.

1102
00:53:26,740 --> 00:53:28,820
我每次回来都很高兴
I do love it when I come.

1103
00:53:28,821 --> 00:53:29,860
那么我也高兴
I'm glad.

1104
00:53:31,740 --> 00:53:32,800
这就是了
That's it.

1105
00:53:32,820 --> 00:53:35,409
你在这儿啊 Alfred
Oh, there you are, Alfred.

1106
00:53:35,410 --> 00:53:37,800
很高兴见到你 喝杯饮料吧
Nice to see you. Have a glass of this.

1107
00:53:37,820 --> 00:53:40,820
- Ivy在吗  - 我在这儿呢
- Is Ivy about?  - I'm just here.

1108
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:46,700
谢谢
Thank you.

1109
00:53:50,740 --> 00:53:53,680
- 葬礼怎么样   - 办的不错
- How was the funeral?  - Was well attended.

1110
00:53:53,700 --> 00:53:56,760
对我妈也算是个宽慰了
So that's something for my mother to hold on to.

1111
00:53:56,780 --> 00:53:58,860
我读了你的信
I read your letter.

1112
00:54:00,780 --> 00:54:02,880
如果伤害了你的感情 那我很抱歉
I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings.

1113
00:54:02,881 --> 00:54:03,720
该道歉的是我
No, I'm sorry.

1114
00:54:03,740 --> 00:54:05,860
我上次过来的时候误会了你的意思
I got the wrong end of the stick when I were last up here,

1115
00:54:05,880 --> 00:54:07,740
但这是我的错
but it were my mistake.

1116
00:54:07,760 --> 00:54:11,700
你的本意 只是想尽量友好的欢迎我
All you did was...try and give me a nice welcome,

1117
00:54:11,720 --> 00:54:13,740
所以你不该抱歉
and you can't feel sorry for that.

1118
00:54:13,760 --> 00:54:14,920
你我能以朋友身份道别吗
We can part as friends?

1119
00:54:14,940 --> 00:54:17,820
当然可以 我可以做到
We can, as far as I'm concerned.

1120
00:54:21,880 --> 00:54:23,840
Daisy在吗
Is Daisy here?

1121
00:54:24,900 --> 00:54:26,524
我想知道
I wanted to see if she

1122
00:54:26,525 --> 00:54:29,700
我和她能不能继续是朋友
and I could be friends an' all before I go.

1123
00:54:29,720 --> 00:54:31,920
她今天去Mason家的农庄了
She's gone to Mr Mason's farm for the day.

1124
00:54:31,940 --> 00:54:34,740
直到晚上才能回来
She won't be back till late.

1125
00:54:39,820 --> 00:54:43,760
Daisy你今天来是为了避开Alfred吗
Daisy, are you here to avoid seeing Alfred?

1126
00:54:43,780 --> 00:54:45,537
Ivy又拒绝了他
Ivy's turned him down again,

1127
00:54:45,538 --> 00:54:47,880
所以他以后应该不会回来了
so he won't come back after today.

1128
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:50,760
Patmore太太对此怎么说
What does Mrs Patmore say about it?

1129
00:54:50,780 --> 00:54:52,820
让我避开他 所以我就这么做了
To stay away so I don't meet him.

1130
00:54:54,780 --> 00:54:56,780
- 我觉得这个想法不对   - 为什么
- I would advise against that.  - But why?

1131
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:58,880
我在这里多待一会你难道不高兴吗
I thought you'd be glad if I stayed a bit longer.

1132
00:54:58,900 --> 00:55:00,547
我自然是希望你不会离开
I wish you'd stay and never leave,

1133
00:55:00,548 --> 00:55:01,920
我希望有朝一日会这样
and I hope you will one day,

1134
00:55:01,940 --> 00:55:04,760
但Patmore太太错了
but Mrs Patmore's wrong.

1135
00:55:06,740 --> 00:55:08,866
Daisy 你一生中
Daisy, there won't be

1136
00:55:08,867 --> 00:55:10,780
爱上的人不会有很多
too many people that you love in your life,

1137
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:12,760
而他是其中之一
and he's one.

1138
00:55:12,780 --> 00:55:15,720
我不知道现在我是怎么想他的
I don't know what I feel about him. Not now.

1139
00:55:15,740 --> 00:55:19,680
即使这样 你也要去和这个年轻人道个别
Even so, you need to say goodbye to this young man,

1140
00:55:19,700 --> 00:55:21,680
在你们两之间
with nothing jagged,

1141
00:55:21,700 --> 00:55:23,880
不要心存遗憾和怨恨
nothing harsh, between you.

1142
00:55:23,900 --> 00:55:26,800
我不知道该说什么
I couldn't think of the words.

1143
00:55:26,820 --> 00:55:28,860
到时候就知道了
We'll find them together.

1144
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:33,880
我会及时把你送回唐顿
And er, we'll get you back to Downton in time.

1145
00:55:35,860 --> 00:55:37,760
你在默默忍受吧
Are you bearing up?

1146
00:55:37,780 --> 00:55:39,800
坐这里
In here.

1147
00:55:39,820 --> 00:55:41,920
我再也见不到Michael了 是不是
I'm never going to see Michael again, am I?

1148
00:55:41,940 --> 00:55:45,206
如果你想去那里找他
If you want to go out there and look for him,

1149
00:55:45,207 --> 00:55:46,840
我会支持你
I'll support you.

1150
00:55:46,860 --> 00:55:48,940
别人已经找过了
They've already done all that.

1151
00:55:49,700 --> 00:55:51,840
警察 私人侦探 能出动的都出动了
Police and private detectives and everything.

1152
00:55:51,860 --> 00:55:53,940
那么你必须耐心
Well, then you must be patient.

1153
00:55:54,700 --> 00:55:57,760
有时我觉得上帝不愿我幸福
Sometimes I feel that God doesn't want me to be happy.

1154
00:55:57,780 --> 00:55:59,920
亲爱的 所有生命都是由麻烦组成的
My dear, all life is a series of problems

1155
00:55:59,940 --> 00:56:02,720
我们必须努力解决
which we must try and solve.

1156
00:56:02,740 --> 00:56:05,860
一个一个的解决
First one, then the next, and the next,...

1157
00:56:07,720 --> 00:56:08,940
直到我们死亡
..Until at last we die.

1158
00:56:12,860 --> 00:56:15,840
不如你给咱拿点冰淇淋吧
Why don't you get us an ice cream?

1159
00:56:15,860 --> 00:56:18,900
对啊 吃点冰一切就解决了
Yes. That should sort it out.

1160
00:56:31,860 --> 00:56:34,392
那不是Gillingham大人吗
Isn't that Lord Gillingham?

1161
00:56:34,393 --> 00:56:35,840
怎么 不会吧 他在哪
What? It can't be. Where?

1162
00:56:38,860 --> 00:56:41,097
Lane Fox小姐会怎么想啊
What does Miss Lane Fox think about it?

1163
00:56:41,098 --> 00:56:41,880
我也很好奇
That's what I wonder.

1164
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:42,712
我同意
I agree.

1165
00:56:42,713 --> 00:56:45,760
他是我知道的最不靠谱的未婚夫了
He's the most unconvincing fiance I've ever come across.

1166
00:56:45,780 --> 00:56:47,840
她可能不知道
Perhaps she doesn't know.

1167
00:56:47,860 --> 00:56:50,940
咱们知道她就知道  这点我很确定
If we know, she knows. You can count on that.

1168
00:56:52,820 --> 00:56:55,880
Green怎么会死了呢
Green. But how could he be dead?

1169
00:56:55,900 --> 00:56:58,720
我也从别人那里听说的
I'm only telling you what they told me.

1170
00:56:58,740 --> 00:57:00,880
他当时在皮卡迪利大街
That he was in Piccadilly and he...

1171
00:56:58,740 --> 00:57:01,880
{\a6}伦敦的繁华街道

1172
00:57:00,900 --> 00:57:04,880
然后他滑倒在马路上
slipped or stumbled and fell into the road.

1173
00:57:04,900 --> 00:57:06,940
我不知该说什么
I don't know what to say.

1174
00:57:07,860 --> 00:57:09,946
咱们昨天刚说完那样的话就出事了
It just seemed so odd after

1175
00:57:09,947 --> 00:57:10,920
我觉得很奇怪
our conversation yesterday

1176
00:57:10,940 --> 00:57:13,860
我觉得我应该亲自告诉你
that I felt that I should... bring you the news myself.

1177
00:57:17,780 --> 00:57:20,900
现在你能告诉我你想让他走人的原因了吗
Can you explain to me now why you wanted him sacked?

1178
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,940
不能
No.

1179
00:57:23,700 --> 00:57:25,680
你好Tony 天哪
Hello, Tony. Heavens,

1180
00:57:25,700 --> 00:57:27,880
今天的集会变得多热闹了啊
what a gathering of the clans today's turning out to be.

1181
00:57:27,900 --> 00:57:29,800
我先离开片刻
Would you excuse me for a moment?

1182
00:57:30,900 --> 00:57:32,424
我猜你回到唐顿
I don't suppose it's a good sign

1183
00:57:32,425 --> 00:57:34,820
是因为出了些不好的事吧
to find you back at Downton?

1184
00:57:35,800 --> 00:57:37,800
确实  发生了点事
Not really. Not this time.

1185
00:57:41,320 --> 00:57:46,360
你是说他跌倒在路上 然后被车撞了 在昨天
You mean he fell into the road and he was hit? Yesterday?

1186
00:57:46,380 --> 00:57:48,460
不是汽车就是卡车
By a bus or lorry, apparently.

1187
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:51,520
有人看到吗
And someone saw this?

1188
00:57:51,540 --> 00:57:55,500
人行道上都挤满了  很多人都目睹了
The pavement was crowded. Lots of people saw it.

1189
00:57:58,540 --> 00:58:02,340
- 这也算是个解脱   - 为何这么说
- That's a relief.  - What do you mean?

1190
00:58:04,340 --> 00:58:07,380
没什么 我只是这么一说
Nothing. I don't mean anything.

1191
00:58:08,420 --> 00:58:10,360
Mary
Mary!

1192
00:58:10,380 --> 00:58:12,520
你妈妈说过我要来吗
Did your mother warn you I was coming?

1193
00:58:12,540 --> 00:58:14,520
她说过
She did.

1194
00:58:14,540 --> 00:58:16,540
为什么你这么快又回到约克郡了
Why are you back in Yorkshire so soon?

1195
00:58:17,300 --> 00:58:18,888
本来不会这么快
I'd no sooner got back than I was

1196
00:58:18,889 --> 00:58:21,440
但我被派到惠特比去参加佃农大会
despatched to a tenant farmers' convention in Whitby.

1197
00:58:21,460 --> 00:58:24,360
可会议已经结束了 我准备从这儿回家
But it's over now, so I'll go home from here.

1198
00:58:24,380 --> 00:58:27,360
- 我能问你个问题吗  - 当然
- Can I ask you something? - Of course.

1199
00:58:27,380 --> 00:58:30,380
- 有点古怪   - 说吧
