妈妈搬去去和克鲁郡的姐姐做邻居
moving to Crewe to be nearer my sister,

1245
01:01:03,380 --> 01:01:05,520
所以我很高兴你来送我 真的
so I'm glad you're here to say goodbye. I really am.

1246
01:01:05,540 --> 01:01:07,460
我给你准备了礼物
I've brought you a present.

1247
01:01:07,480 --> 01:01:10,460
Mason先生做的 整整一篮子
Mr Mason's made you a basket full of things.

1248
01:01:10,480 --> 01:01:13,420
肉卷 奶酪 火腿 果酱和咸菜
Rolls and cheese and ham, and jams and pickles,

1249
01:01:13,440 --> 01:01:14,865
还放了些苹果汁
and he's put some cider in too,

1250
01:01:14,866 --> 01:01:16,520
是给你在路上吃的
to keep you going on the train home.

1251
01:01:16,540 --> 01:01:18,237
他真好 Daisy
That was kind of him, Daisy.

1252
01:01:18,238 --> 01:01:20,480
你确定这些不是给你做的
Are you sure it wasn't meant for you?

1253
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:22,400
不 他是为Alfred准备的
No, he did it for Alfred.

1254
01:01:22,420 --> 01:01:25,400
我告诉他我们是老朋友 他就做了这些
I told him we were old friends, so he did it for you.

1255
01:01:33,380 --> 01:01:35,360
--你知道Ivy拒绝我了吧   -是的
- You know Ivy turned me down? - I do, yes.

1256
01:01:35,380 --> 01:01:37,540
我想我在对待她上有点犯傻
I think I've been a bit blind where she's concerned.

1257
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:39,400
爱情本来就是犯傻
Love is blind.

1258
01:01:39,420 --> 01:01:42,460
也许吧 我在想我是不是又做了傻事
Maybe. But I wonder now I've not been a fool.

1259
01:01:42,480 --> 01:01:46,280
你对我一直都这么好 这么真诚
You've always been so good to me, Daisy. So true.

1260
01:01:46,300 --> 01:01:47,500
可我却一直没注意到
But I could never see it.

1261
01:01:47,520 --> 01:01:51,360
谢谢你 我很高兴
That's kind of you to say, and good to hear.

1262
01:01:52,500 --> 01:01:55,480
我爱过你 Alfred 我不会否认
I loved you, Alfred. I'll not deny it.

1263
01:01:55,500 --> 01:01:59,480
但现在一切都结束了 我们也无法回到从前
But that's done with now, and what I felt won't come back.

1264
01:01:59,500 --> 01:02:02,380
是时候你走你的 我走我的了
It's time for you to go your way and me to go mine.

1265
01:02:03,380 --> 01:02:04,487
你会祝福我吧
But you wish me well?

1266
01:02:04,488 --> 01:02:06,480
是的 我真心祝福你 Alfred
Oh, I do, Alfred, yeah.

1267
01:02:06,500 --> 01:02:09,320
那就好 那就很好了
So well. So very well.

1268
01:02:09,340 --> 01:02:10,520
永远是朋友
Friends forever.

1269
01:02:11,500 --> 01:02:13,500
永远是朋友 Daisy
Friends forever, Daisy.

1270
01:02:17,420 --> 01:02:19,520
好的 现在我真的得走了
Right, now this really is goodbye.

1271
01:02:30,360 --> 01:02:32,480
你还好吗Daisy
Are you all right, Daisy?

1272
01:02:32,500 --> 01:02:36,420
我去储藏室换上围裙
I'll just get this off and pop in the pantry for my apron.

1273
01:02:51,540 --> 01:02:53,540
好了 就是这样了
Well, that's that, then.

1274
01:02:58,300 --> 01:03:01,420
当你拿出那个篮子
Do you know, when you brought up that basket,...

1275
01:03:02,420 --> 01:03:07,320
我真是为你骄傲 差点哭了
..I were so proud of you, I felt like crying out.

1276
01:03:07,340 --> 01:03:10,360
就算你是我的女儿
If you were my own daughter,

1277
01:03:10,380 --> 01:03:13,360
我也不可能比现在更自豪了
I couldn't be prouder than I am now.

1278
01:03:30,540 --> 01:03:33,376
你知道我今天为什么来吗
You do know why I came today.

1279
01:03:33,377 --> 01:03:34,440
来看义卖
To see the bazaar.

1280
01:03:34,460 --> 01:03:36,400
是来看你
To see you.

1281
01:03:37,440 --> 01:03:41,500
令我惊讶的是 我发现 自从我走后
I find - perhaps to my surprise - that since I left,

1282
01:03:41,520 --> 01:03:43,480
我就一直想着你
I can't think of anything but you.

1283
01:03:43,500 --> 01:03:46,340
我也很惊讶
To your surprise and my surprise.

1284
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:49,320
我只是不想放过机会
I'm only asking for a chance.

1285
01:03:50,420 --> 01:03:52,500
真的有会议在惠特比举行吗
Was there really a conference in Whitby?

1286
01:03:53,540 --> 01:03:55,380
当然没有
Of course not.

1287
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:58,180
你真让我受宠若惊
I'm flattered,

1288
01:03:58,181 --> 01:04:00,420
Charles 还有感动
Charles, and even moved.

1289
01:04:00,440 --> 01:04:04,520
但与其再在名单上添加一个对我灰心的男人
But rather than add to the list of men I've disappointed,

1290
01:04:04,540 --> 01:04:07,820
现在拒绝你可能会更好些
it might be kinder to refuse you now

1291
01:04:07,821 --> 01:04:09,460
你也会释怀些
and let you off the hook.

1292
01:04:10,500 --> 01:04:14,440
恐怕我是不会允许你这么做的
Hmm, I'm afraid I couldn't allow that.

1293
01:04:17,500 --> 01:04:19,420
至少得让我放手一搏
Not without putting up a fight.

1294
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:34,400
你怎么还在这里啊
What are you still doing here?

1295
01:04:34,420 --> 01:04:36,440
我想知道你昨天做了什么
I wish I knew what you were up to yesterday.

1296
01:04:36,460 --> 01:04:40,340
- 为什么要出门  - 我只是想出趟门
- Why did you go?   - I wanted to get away.

1297
01:04:41,360 --> 01:04:43,500
你没有做什么傻事吧
You'd never do anything foolish, would you?

1298
01:04:43,520 --> 01:04:47,340
你绝不会拿我们的一切去冒险吧
You'd never risk everything we've built together?

1299
01:04:47,360 --> 01:04:49,380
当然不会 你了解我
Certainly not. You know me.

1300
01:04:49,400 --> 01:04:50,561
当我想要做一件事时
When I do a thing, I like

1301
01:04:50,562 --> 01:04:52,420
都是会有一个非常充分的理由的
to have a very good reason for doing it.

1302
01:05:08,300 --> 01:05:09,480
你们两躲到哪里去了
Where have you two been hiding?

1303
01:05:09,500 --> 01:05:12,320
视野良好的地方  魔术师们的最佳藏匿处
In plain view, where all good tricksters hide.

1304
01:05:12,340 --> 01:05:14,320
看看我找到了什么  Tom找找看
Look what I've found. Tom, will you see

1305
01:05:14,340 --> 01:05:16,480
桌子上还有没有干净酒杯
if there are some clean glasses on that table?

1306
01:05:17,460 --> 01:05:21,300
非常好亲爱的 大获全胜啊
Well done, my dear. A real triumph.

1307
01:05:22,360 --> 01:05:23,460
但愿吧
I hope so.

1308
01:05:23,480 --> 01:05:26,440
我让大家明天再清扫场地
I've told them they can clear up the rest tomorrow.

1309
01:05:26,460 --> 01:05:29,360
我觉得这是历史上最好的一次义卖
I thought that was the best bazaar I've known here.

1310
01:05:29,380 --> 01:05:32,500
没错 在我们这代人以后最好的
Certainly. At least since your father and I were running it.

1311
01:05:34,380 --> 01:05:37,280
现在 我作为一个归家的海外浪人丈夫
And now, as the Prodigal Husband home from the sea,

1312
01:05:37,300 --> 01:05:39,520
让我为我的贤妻祝酒
let me raise a glass to my extraordinary wife

1313
01:05:39,540 --> 01:05:44,340
她把一切都打理的比我在家时好
who can clearly manage far better in my absence. Cora.

1314
01:05:44,360 --> 01:05:45,370
敬Grantham夫人
Lady Grantham.

1315
01:05:45,371 --> 01:05:46,380
敬Cora  - 敬妈妈
Cora.  - Mama.

1316
01:05:46,400 --> 01:05:48,121
非常出色 Grantham夫人
Very well done, Lady Grantham.

1317
01:05:48,122 --> 01:05:50,360
现在我恐怕得走了
And now, I'm afraid, I should be going.

1318
01:05:50,380 --> 01:05:52,300
你能来真好
It was so kind of you to come.

1319
01:05:52,320 --> 01:05:53,355
我估计这次
I don't suppose I could

1320
01:05:53,356 --> 01:05:55,380
- 搭不了你的顺风车了吧 我坐火车来的
- ask YOU for a lift this time?  - I came by train

1321
01:05:55,400 --> 01:05:58,360
- 我更喜欢驾车  - 当然
- but I'd much rather drive.  - Certainly.

1322
01:05:58,480 --> 01:06:00,380
我送送你们
I'll see you off.

1323
01:06:04,440 --> 01:06:06,016
我离开期间
What sort of menage has

1324
01:06:06,017 --> 01:06:08,540
到底发生了什么啊
that turned into while I've been away?

